2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 35
BY SENATOR HODGES
A RESOLUTION
To commend Sheriff Jason Ard and the Livingston Parish Sheriff's Office for their
exceptional efforts in combating illegal narcotics trafficking and protecting children
through the Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force.
WHEREAS, the protection of the residents of Louisiana, particularly children, from
the dangers of illegal narcotics and exploitation, is one of the most solemn responsibilities
of law enforcement and the state; and
WHEREAS, under the leadership of Sheriff Jason Ard, the Livingston Parish
Sheriff's Office has demonstrated unwavering commitment to public safety through
aggressive enforcement, strategic partnerships, and proactive investigative efforts; and
WHEREAS, in February 2026, the Livingston Parish Sheriff's Office Narcotics
Division conducted a historic seizure of approximately three hundred sixty-one pounds of
methamphetamine, valued at an estimated four million dollars, representing the largest drug
seizure in the agency's history and one of the largest in the state of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, this significant operation resulted in the confiscation of additional
evidence including digital weighing scales, packaging materials, United States currency, and
a vehicle, further disrupting a large-scale drug trafficking enterprise; and
WHEREAS, the success of this operation was made possible through collaboration
with multiple law enforcement agencies, including Homeland Security Investigations, the
Houston Police Department High Intensity Drug Trafficking Areas Program, the Splendora
Police Department in Texas, and the St. James Parish Sheriff's Office; and
WHEREAS, in December 2024, the Livingston Parish Sheriff's Office achieved the
largest fentanyl seizure in the parish's history, removing approximately one hundred
thousand lethal doses of fentanyl from circulation and thereby preventing potentially
catastrophic loss of life; and
WHEREAS, this extensive investigation, spanning over two years, resulted in
