multiple arrests and the seizure of fentanyl, oxycodone, methamphetamine, and vehicles
connected to narcotics distribution, reflecting the diligence and persistence of the narcotics
division; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Ard has continued to strengthen the narcotics division by
increasing personnel and resources, enhancing the agency's ability to identify, investigate,
and apprehend individuals engaged in illegal drug activity; and
WHEREAS, in October 2023, under Sheriff Ard's leadership, the Livingston Parish
Sheriff's Office launched and expanded its Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force in
partnership with the Louisiana Attorney General's Office; and
WHEREAS, investigations conducted by the task force in 2024, extended into
twenty-four states and five countries, highlighting the widespread and borderless nature of
internet-facilitated crimes against children; and
WHEREAS, a three-day sting operation conducted by the task force in February
2025, resulted in the arrest of eleven individuals facing charges related to child exploitation;
and
WHEREAS, the sting operation was conducted in collaboration with Chris Hansen,
widely known for his work on Dateline NBC and the investigative segment To Catch a
Predator, as well as his web series Takedown with Chris Hansen produced for the streaming
service TruBlu; and
WHEREAS, during 2025, Sheriff Ard, the Livingston Parish Internet Crimes Against
Children Task Force, and Chris Hansen collaborated multiple times to conduct sting
operations, with the collaborations not only seeking to support law enforcement efforts, but
to educate the public regarding tactics used by online predators and the evolving dangers
children face in digital spaces; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Ard and his team have emphasized the importance of
community education, interagency cooperation, and the use of advanced technology in
addressing evolving threats to children and communities; and
WHEREAS, the combined efforts of narcotics enforcement and child protection
initiatives have significantly enhanced the safety and well-being of the residents of
Livingston Parish and the state of Louisiana.
